## 📋 Quick Recipe (Copy/Paste Ready)

Here's the **complete sequence** assuming standard home network `192.168.1.0/24`:

```bash
# 1. Check what subnet you're on
ip addr show | grep "inet " | grep -v 127.0.0.1
# (confirm the IP, e.g., 192.168.1.42)

# 2. Install UFW if missing
sudo apt install ufw

# 3. Set safe defaults
sudo ufw default deny incoming
sudo ufw default allow outgoing

# 4. Allow Vite from local subnet only
sudo ufw allow from 192.168.1.0/24 to any port 5173 proto tcp

# 5. (Optional) Allow SSH from local subnet
# sudo ufw allow from 192.168.1.0/24 to any port 22 proto tcp

# 6. Enable UFW
sudo ufw enable

# 7. Verify
sudo ufw status numbered
```

