## 🎓 Security Lesson Embedded

What you just did is a microcosm of good security practice:
- ✅ **Principle of least privilege** — only allow what's needed
- ✅ **Network segmentation** — restrict to known trusted network
- ✅ **Defense in depth** — even if your router has issues, UFW provides another layer
- ✅ **Default deny** — block by default, allow specifically

This same mindset applies to production apps: in v3+ when we add auth, we'll apply similar "default deny, allow specific" patterns to user permissions. 👏

